task_description: Facing the building to your West (approx. 258°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: To estimate the building's height, I first need to see its full extent, so I will tilt my view upwards to see the roof.
I have seen the top of the building, and now I need to see the bottom to gauge the full height, so I will tilt my view downwards.

Having viewed the top and bottom of the building, I can estimate its height by counting the floors; it appears to have about 6 floors, and assuming a standard height of 4 meters per floor including structure and ceiling space, the total height is approximately 24 meters.
